		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top">What's between Bronze and Ro?<br clear=all>
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Tue, Sep 5th 7:41 AM2000 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/db/classes.html?class=6&mid=96815406817112&post=1"><a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=6&mid=96815406817112&num=4&page=&post=1&replyto=96815406817112"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=96815406817112></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Anonymous&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Hey everyone - So I've got a 20 Pally, and have slowly been able to save some money to make the transition from banded to bronze. My question is, now what? Do I just stay content with my tin-man look and perpetual encumbered-ness until am high enough to forge my own Armor of Ro? Or is there some intermediary armor that's obtainable for a 20-30 Pally?<br><br>I know it's a general question (since there's a lot of armor out there that seems attrative), but I'm curious if there's any mid-level armor that's particularly good/popular for a 20-30 Paladin (and won't take months of camping or cost thousands of plat).<br><br>Durim Brightblade<br>20th Circle Paladin<br>Prexus Server</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >4 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
		   <table class="mform2"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform2" valign="top">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Tue, Sep 5th 2:34 PM2000 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=6&mid=96815406817112&num=4&page=&post=1&replyto=9681788673677"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=9681788673677></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=605"><span id=>Kilraven</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br>37 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.50]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Kilraven&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Ro is going to be very difficult (if not impossible in some cases) for you to get without buying a piece. You're going to find you'll be stuck with bronze for awhile, but that could change since there are new armors to made with a blacksmithing skill (armor pieces made through blacksmithing weighs a lot less than bronze I believe). However, you want to try for No Drop pieces, you can try Lower Guk and get some Shin Greaves (they're not that rare of a drop, and are normally rotting away on corpses since they're No Drop). You can also try to get Icy Greaves from Permafrost. And in Sol A there are some No Drop pieces to be had. Even though all of these dungeons are nice for the 20-30 range, they do require grouping too. Keep in mind the closer you get to 30, the easier it is to get some of the materials for the Ro armor.</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >1 Replies</td></tr></table><table width="100%"><tr><td class=mhback>&nbsp;</td><td class=mhback >Thread Subject</a></td><td class=mhback>Started by</a></td><td class=mhback>Replies</a></td><td class=mhback>Last Post</a></td><td class=mhback>Rating</a></td></tr><tr class=mdr>
