		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.50]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=GiddyGonzalus&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>I don't want my story to discourage you, but .... at level 33 I'm still in bronze armour. I have managed to pick up a Skull Shaped Barbute and Carnal Pauldrons, but the rest is bronze. Why? Probably my own fault. I've been more interested in getting xp than in going to Sol. However, if it's armour you want then you HAVE to go to Sol A and B. I picked up my Carnal Pauldrons there by waiting around (outside of a group since the levels there were high 30s, mid 40s)and healing the group that was camping the spawn that dropped them. Since they had all gotten the CP, they let me loot them. You can pick up a number of items this way since a lot of them are No Drop. Heck I know a lot of people who have even picked up their Mith BP this way.<br>The other thing to do (something I've been loathe to do until lately), is to camp items to sell. This seems the best way to make a plat as there are few critters that drop good loot until you're in your mid 30s.<br>BTW, Armour of Ro is virtually unattainable without some high level help (or until you're high enough level that you're looking for Plane Armour instead). I've got many of the elements to make Ro, but I am lacking the one major ingredient ... Mistmoore Granite. The best way to get it is with the help of some HIGH level friends/guildmates. I know of too many Paladins that have gone into MM to get the Granite and come out 2 or 3 levels lower empty handed and REALLY pissed off.<br>Good luck and I hope this helps. It's not great, but gives a little insight into someone who feels your pain.</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>________<br><br>I've travelled this world and have seen many wondrous things. You are not one of them.</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
